<div class="wb">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="home-section">
            <h3 class="">Executive Summary</h3>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <p class="follow-up">Successful Audit requires that Auditors and school staff conduct themselves professionally, fairly and courteously throughout the Audit. Auditors will aim to leave the staff of each school feeling that they have gained from the experience of Audit and are better equipped to meet students’ needs. The focus of our Audit is to find out what a school is doing well and what needs to be improved in order to strengthen further students’ achievement and well-being. The size of the Audit team is based on the circumstances of the school and the number of students registered. Lead Auditors and team Auditors are specifically trained to manage the Audit process. They have no direct connectivity with the school being audited. The school is notified of the Audit 5 working days prior to the start of the Audit.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6"><img class="section-side-image" src="https://eduvationgroup.com/img/new-blur-audit.png">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="lb">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="home-section">
            <div class="row">
                <h3 class="">Auditors will</h3>

                <ul>
                    <li>Arrive at fair and accurate judgements that are securely based on evidence, in line with the our Audit Framework;</li>

                    <li>Make their evaluations impartially, free of personal bias or prejudice; </li>

                    <li> Treat those they meet during the Audit process with courtesy and respect, keeping the interests of students at the heart of every Audit;</li>

                    <li>Establish effective working relationships with the school staff;</li>

                    <li>  Respect the confidentiality of information; however, to report any safeguarding concerns directly to the school top management.</li>

                    <li> Plan and manage the Audit process effectively to ensure it is as smooth and straightforward as possible.</li>

                    <li>Take into account policies, documentation and self-evaluation undertaken by the school and, explore issues through professional dialogue with school staff;</li>

                    <li> Observe students’ learning experiences directly; scrutinise work; engage in discussions with students, staff and governors;</li>

                    <li> Offer up to five joint lesson observations with the principal/head; </li>

                    <li>analyse and feedback headline responses from parent and student questionnaires;</li>

                    <li>Feedback Audit outcomes to school staff and governing bodies orally to be followed by a written report identifying the school’s strengths and where improvement is needed.</li>

                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center">
                <br>
